  "text": "Epigenetic roles. Consistent with their roles in differentiation and development, a range of genetic and biochemical evidence suggests that a major function of many small RNAs and lncRNAs is the regulation of epigenetic processes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , probably by guiding chromatin-modifying enzymes to their sites of action and/or by acting as scaffolds for chromosomal organization [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] (FIG. 4) .",
